na for myself (I have the benefit of being mostly Canadian and not having to adjust my accent for the latter two) broadened the sensuality of the book, and not just because the sounds were resounding in my head. I could feel the words filling my lungs, or burning my throat, or passing through my airways in different manners, so that saying the words on the page, those already sensual words, made the sensuality tangible for me. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eTo feel a book in other ways as I read it and hear it is as near as I come to a holy experience. Words are my church. Michael Ondaatje is my priest. The English Patient is one of my scriptures. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eDon't even talk to me about the travesty that is the film. ","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"faves","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=faves"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"booker-prize","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=booker-prize"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"canadian-lit","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=canadian-lit"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"the-best","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=the-best"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"to-read-again","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=to-read-again"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"about-love","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=about-love"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"about-guilt","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1022982?shelf=about-guilt"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/18620